http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Tragic-end-to-pilgrimage/article13989803.ece

Mary Lisha, 32, of Baiju Sadanam at Moothakara in Kollam city who was killed in the bus accident at Tirunelveli on Friday morning was to have celebrated her wedding anniversary on Tuesday.Her one-and-a-half-year-old son Alroy was also killed in the accident. Along with her husband Baiju Muthunayakam and elder son Aaron, they had gone on a pilgrimage to Velankanni as part of a package tour on January 5.Baiju and the elder son, who sustained serious injuries in the accident, are admitted to a private hospital in Thiruvananthapuram.Baiju who is employed in the Gulf, came down for Christmas holiday and is scheduled to return on January 17.Mary Lisha, whose parents are in Kanyakumari district of Tamil Nadu, visited them on Thursday on the return trip from Velankanni. The funeral rites of the mother and son will take place at Moothakara parish church on Saturday.Mary Lisha, 32, and her one-and-a-half-year-old son Alroy were killed in the accident.